# Office Inventory Dashboard System Specification (SELISE)

## 1. Problem / Why
Currently, office inventory requests (e.g., notepads, stationery, snacks, slippers) are handled through informal communication such as verbal requests or chat messages. This causes:

* Lost or delayed requests
* No tracking visibility for employees
* Manual stock update errors
* No approval workflow
* No usage analytics for administrators

Additionally, there is no centralized login mechanism to control system access.
To solve these issues, a role-based Office Inventory Dashboard system with a secure login page, employee request interface, and admin inventory management panel is required.

---

## 2. User Stories

### Employee User Stories

* As an employee, I want to log in securely using my office email.
* As an employee, I want to submit inventory requests easily.
* As an employee, I want my personal details auto-filled.
* As an employee, I want to track request status (Pending / Approved / Rejected).
* As an employee, I want to view my request history.
* As an employee, I want notifications when request status changes.
* As an employee, I want to suggest new inventory items.
### Admin User Stories

* As an admin, I want to log in securely.
* As an admin, I want to view all incoming requests.
* As an admin, I want to approve or reject requests.
* As an admin, I want inventory to update automatically after approval.
* As an admin, I want to monitor stock levels.
* As an admin, I want alerts for low stock items.
* As an admin, I want to generate usage analytics reports.

---

## 3. Acceptance Criteria

### Login Page

* User must enter email
* User must enter password
* User must select role (Admin or Employee)
* Login must redirect user to correct dashboard
* SELISE logo must be displayed
* SELISE background image must be displayed

### Employee Dashboard

Employee must be able to:

* Submit request with:

  * Item name
  * Quantity
  * Purpose
  * Urgency level

System must:

* Auto-fill employee name, department, email
* Show request status:

  * Pending (Yellow)
  * Approved (Green)
  * Rejected (Red)
* Show request history
* Show notifications when request updated

### Admin Dashboard

Admin must be able to:

* View all requests
* Approve requests
* Reject requests
* Add comments
* Update inventory automatically after approval
* Edit stock manually if needed

### Inventory Module

System must:

* Display real-time stock levels
* Show low-stock alerts
* Allow adding new inventory items

### Reports Module

Admin must be able to:

* View most requested items
* View monthly reports
* View quarterly reports
* Export reports (CSV / PDF)

